# Mini Library Management System

This is a simple Python-based Library Management System built for the Object-Oriented Programming 1 course at Limkokwing University.

## Project Structure

- `operations.py` – Core functions for managing books and members
- `demo.py` – Demonstration script showing how the system works
- `tests.py` – Unit tests using assert statements
- `DesignRationale.pdf` – Explanation of design choices
- `UML.png` – Hand-drawn UML diagram
- `README.md` – This file

## How to Run

1. Open the project in PyCharm
2. Run `demo.py` to see the system in action
3. Run `tests.py` to verify functionality

## Features

- Add, update, delete books and members
- Search books by title or author
- Borrow and return books (limit: 3 per member)
- Valid genre enforcement using tuples
- Data stored in dictionaries and lists

